# IFrame Content Extraction Feature (Revised)

## Overview

The extension currently only extracts content from the main `document`. This plan adds full iframe-aware extraction using the native extension platform approach: `all_frames: true` injects the extractor content script into **every frame** (same-origin and cross-origin alike), and `chrome.webNavigation.getAllFrames()` provides the full frame hierarchy with stable `frameId`s. The background then targets specific frames via `chrome.tabs.sendMessage(tabId, msg, { frameId })`.

This is architecturally cleaner than trying to access `iframe.contentDocument` from the parent frame and avoids any same-origin/cross-origin distinction at the extraction layer.

---

## Proposed Changes

### 1 — Manifests — Enable all-frames injection

#### [MODIFY] [manifest.chrome.json](file:///m:/.systemfile/webpage-content-extractor-extension/manifest.chrome.json)

Two changes:
1. Add `"webNavigation"` to `"permissions"` (needed for `chrome.webNavigation.getAllFrames`).
2. Add `"all_frames": true` and `"match_about_blank": true` to the `content_scripts` entry.

```diff
 "permissions": [
     "activeTab",
     "clipboardWrite",
     "storage",
     "scripting",
-    "tabs"
+    "tabs",
+    "webNavigation"
 ],
 
 "content_scripts": [{
     "matches": ["<all_urls>"],
+    "all_frames": true,
+    "match_about_blank": true,
     "css": ["content/sidebar.css", "content/chatbot_injector.css"],
     "js": ["content/extractor.js", "content/sidebar.js", "content/chatbot_injector.js"],
     "run_at": "document_idle"
 }]
```

#### [MODIFY] [manifest.firefox.json](file:///m:/.systemfile/webpage-content-extractor-extension/manifest.firefox.json)

Same two changes as above (Firefox supports both `all_frames` and `webNavigation`).

> [!NOTE]
> `sidebar.js` and `chatbot_injector.js` will also run in sub-frames with `all_frames: true`. They already guard against double injection (`if (document.getElementById('wce-ai-sidebar-container')) return;`), and the chatbot injector only activates if the current URL matches a known chatbot. Neither will cause issues in iframes, but we should add a quick `window === window.top` guard to `sidebar.ts` and `chatbot_injector.ts` to skip injection entirely when running inside a sub-frame — keeping things clean.

---

### 2 — `content/extractor.ts` — Add `getIframes` message handler

#### [MODIFY] [extractor.ts](file:///m:/.systemfile/webpage-content-extractor-extension/content/extractor.ts)

**No need for document-adapter complexity.** Because each frame runs its own instance of the content script with its own `document`, the existing three algorithms work unchanged on every frame. The only changes needed are:

**a) New message action: `getFrameInfo`**

Each frame's extractor responds with its own identity when asked:

```ts
if (request.action === 'getFrameInfo') {
    sendResponse({
        success: true,
        title: document.title,
        url: window.location.href
    });
    return true;
}
```

This lets the background cross-reference `webNavigation` frame data with live page titles.

**b) Extend `extractContent` handler**

The existing handler already works as-is — it extracts from its own `document`. No changes needed to the extraction logic itself.

**c) Add `iframeSource` awareness (optional label in output)**

When `request.iframeSource` is present and `!== 'main'`, the extractor can prefix its output with a context header like `=== Frame: [title] ([url]) ===` so the caller can assemble a merged result. The logic for combining results lives in the background, not here.

---

### 3 — `background.js` — Frame discovery + targeted extraction

#### [MODIFY] [background.js](file:///m:/.systemfile/webpage-content-extractor-extension/background.js)

**a) New handler: `getIframesForTab`**

```js
} else if (request.action === 'getIframesForTab') {
    const { tabId } = request;
    try {
        // Get all frames in the tab (requires webNavigation permission)
        const frames = await chrome.webNavigation.getAllFrames({ tabId });
        if (!frames) { sendResponse({ success: true, frames: [] }); return true; }

        // Build a map of frameId → frame info
        const frameMap = {};
        frames.forEach(f => {
            frameMap[f.frameId] = {
                frameId: f.frameId,
                parentFrameId: f.parentFrameId,
                url: f.url,
                label: '',       // computed below
                path: [],        // computed below
                children: []
            };
        });

        // Build hierarchy (parentFrameId === -1 is the main frame)
        const roots = [];
        frames.forEach(f => {
            if (f.parentFrameId === -1 || f.parentFrameId === 0) {
                if (f.frameId === 0) return; // skip main frame itself
                roots.push(frameMap[f.frameId]);
            } else {
                const parent = frameMap[f.parentFrameId];
                if (parent) parent.children.push(frameMap[f.frameId]);
            }
        });

        // Assign hierarchical labels recursively
        let iframeCounter = {};
        function assignLabels(node, parentLabel) {
            const idx = iframeCounter[parentLabel] = (iframeCounter[parentLabel] || 0);
            iframeCounter[parentLabel]++;
            const seg = `iframe-${idx}`;
            node.label = parentLabel ? `${parentLabel} > ${seg}` : seg;
            node.path = parentLabel ? [...parentLabel.split(' > '), seg] : [seg];
            node.children.forEach(child => assignLabels(child, node.label));
        }
        roots.forEach(r => assignLabels(r, 'main'));

        // Flatten back to a list for easy consumption
        const flat = [];
        function flatten(node) { flat.push(node); node.children.forEach(flatten); }
        roots.forEach(flatten);

        sendResponse({ success: true, frames: flat });
    } catch (err) {
        console.error('[WCE] getIframesForTab error:', err);
        sendResponse({ success: false, frames: [] });
    }
    return true;
```

**b) New handler: `extractFromFrames`**

Used by both the popup and the injector. Extracts from a set of `{ tabId, frameId }` targets and assembles a merged result:

```js
} else if (request.action === 'extractFromFrames') {
    const { tabId, frameTargets, characterLimit, algorithm, iframeSource } = request;
    // frameTargets: Array<{ frameId, label }>
    // iframeSource: 'main' | 'iframes' | 'both'

    const results = [];

    // Main frame (frameId = 0)
    if (iframeSource === 'main' || iframeSource === 'both') {
        try {
            const resp = await chrome.tabs.sendMessage(tabId,
                { action: 'extractContent', characterLimit, promptLength: 0, algorithm },
                { frameId: 0 }
            );
            if (resp?.success) {
                results.push(iframeSource === 'both'
                    ? `=== Main Document ===\n${resp.content}`
                    : resp.content);
            }
        } catch (e) { console.warn('[WCE] main frame extraction failed', e); }
    }

    // Selected iframe frames
    if (iframeSource === 'iframes' || iframeSource === 'both') {
        for (const target of frameTargets) {
            try {
                const resp = await chrome.tabs.sendMessage(tabId,
                    { action: 'extractContent', characterLimit, promptLength: 0, algorithm },
                    { frameId: target.frameId }
                );
                if (resp?.success) {
                    results.push(`=== Frame: ${target.label} ===\n${resp.content}`);
                }
            } catch (e) {
                console.warn(`[WCE] frame ${target.frameId} extraction failed`, e);
                results.push(`=== Frame: ${target.label} ===\n[Extraction failed]`);
            }
        }
    }

    sendResponse({ success: true, content: results.join('\n\n') });
    return true;
```

**c) Update `extractFromTabs` handler**

Forward `iframeSource` and `selectedFrameTargets` fields so the injector can also use the frame-targeted extraction path.

