### 6 — `content/chatbot_injector.ts` — Source selector in popover

#### [MODIFY] [chatbot_injector.ts](file:///m:/.systemfile/webpage-content-extractor-extension/content/chatbot_injector.ts)

In `openTabsPopover`, add a small "Extract From" radio group above the footer using existing `wce-pop-item` styles:

```
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Extract From
◉ Main Document   ○ Iframes   ○ Both
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
```

When clicking **Extract & Insert**, read the selected radio value and pass `iframeSource` (and empty `frameTargets` for default-first-frame behavior) in the `extractFromTabs` / `extractFromFrames` message to background.

> [!NOTE]
> For the injector, we use the "first available iframe" default (no per-tab iframe picker) since showing a per-frame picker for multiple simultaneously-selected tabs would be overly complex. This is the right tradeoff for v1.

